inn1.comm: mild appeal for lbw first ball. It was a full delivery on the legs and Simmons, like he did in the last game, missed out on an opportunity to flick/glance. The ball rolls off the pad
shuffles across to tap this length delivery to point region
beaten! full delivery outside off and Simmons stumbles out and pushes his bat inside the line. Hmmm
around the off stump line, on a length, defended to the off side
full in length, around 86 mph, angling away from Simmons who lets it go through to the keeper
in the zone outside off stump, sort of held its line a touch, left alone
tossed up, from round the stumps, Smith shuffles right across outside off and edges the defensive push to pad
gets across to cut this but straight to  backward point
turns after landing on a length outside off, Smith pushes it to the off side
straighter, closer to the off, worked to the on side
gets down the track but doesn't reach the pitch of the ball and lunges out to defend. The ball bounds off the pad
gets right back and just when you thought he will never get his bat around in time, and there seemed to be an lbw appeal looming in the air, he got his bat across and worked the ball past square-leg
from wide of the crease- that right arm doesn't kick into action as we saw the other day- around off and middle, tapped to the on side
falls over a touch at release, and slants this full delivery in, tapped to the on side
Peach! This one held its line outside off stump and Smith is beaten, stabbing inside the line. Delivered a touch closer to the stumps and he got that to straighten
back to wide of the crease and Smith leans across to defend this to covers
pushes this down the leg side as he fell a touch at release and the ball clipped the pad and goes to fine-leg boundary
Crunchy! He has 1001 ODI runs now. It was a short of length delivery outside off and he crouched and cut it to right of third man
pushes to short fine-leg for a single
gets down the track but Hafeez slows up the pace. Very clever. He didn't push it through but slowed up the pace and Smith had to wait and wait before tapping it to the on side
backs away but mistimes the drive to mid-on
threatens to go to the leg side, moves back into position and clips the ball on the leg stump line to square-leg
Thump! he rushed down the track, didn't reach the pitch of the ball as the bowler shortened the length but he adjusted superbly to whack it high over midwicket boundary.
leans forward to stab it of the inside edge to the on side
shuffles across the stumps to defend it to the off side
full delivery outside off, Simmons reaches out , bat away from the body, and slashes/edges it to third man
reaches forward to jab this full-length delivery to the leg side
short in length, around off, coming in with that angle, Smith shuffles across, raises his front leg in the air and swats the ball past square-leg
Fine cut. It was short in length and there was some width outside off, and he rocked back to cut it hard to backward point boundary
gets forward to nudge this to the leg side
floated from over the wicket this time, pushed close on the off side and they rush across for a good quick single
loud cry for lbw but there was an inside edge. It landed on the middle stump line and turned just about .. Smith jabs at it , and gets an inside edge, I think, on to his pad

Given out lbw but the point of impact was just outside off stump. He went back, shuffled across, and again, like the last game, and even on the previous delivery, stabbed outside the line of the ball, trying to waft across the line. Clueless. The ball landed just outside off and skidded towards off. It would have hit off but the impact was outside off and he was playing a shot.
flighted from round the stumps, pushed out to the off side.
turns away from the off stump, cut away to covers
drifts to the pad, moves past the waft and runs off the pad to fine-leg region
wayward delivery outside the off stump, Bravo flashes his bat at it but makes no contact. The ball flies over the bat
Another wild swing and a miss! fuller and outside off stump, Bravo goes for a big off drive, doesn't lean into the shot, and is beaten
this time he lets the ball go through to the keeper. Wonder whether it was because of the last two deliveries or because of the length- it was on a good length this time, not short or full.
stays back to guide this down to third man for his first run
up and over mid-off. It was a back of length delivery angling away and he went for the punchy on-the-up shot over mid-off, who was well inside the 30-yard, trying to stop the single.
Ah! he has laced that. Full pitched outside off and a lot closer to him and he leaned across to caress it through wide mid-off region. Delicious! And he holds his pose!
moves outside leg, Hafeez follows him, turned to midwicket
leans forward to drive to mid-off
pushes this wide of mid-off for a single
slip and leg gully watch Simmons press back and whip this leg-side delivery to deep square-leg
gets forward to defend this one to the leg side. Still a touch tentative against spin
on the middle and off, Bravo gets back to create room and punches it from the stumps to covers
on the off stump line, defended off the back foot
Forced away! he fetched the length delivery from around off stump line and dragged it powerfully to left of mid-on where the fielder dives to his left, gets some hand on it but can't prevent it.
pushes this past the non striker
Lovely square drive on a bent knee! It was overpitched outside off, very full, and Simmons went down on his knee and unfurled a stylish square drive.
a length delivery on the middle, tapped to the on side
from close to the stumps, on a length, on the middle and leg, jabbed away to the on side
Four on resumption. It was slightly short in length and some width outside off, and he pushed back to cut it through covers!
on the middle stump line, turning, Bravo gets the bat in front of the pad to defend

Missed run out of Bravo The bowler fails to collect the throw from Salman. It was on middle and leg and it went off the pad to the leg side. Salman rushed across, picked the ball and threw it on the bounce. Hafeez was behind the stumps but it bounced a touch more than he anticipated and he fumbled.
leans forward to defend to the off side
gets down the track to push this to mid-off for a single
slightly short of length, outside off,  forced away to long-off
shortish, just outside off, delivered from very close to the stumps, Bravo stabs it in the air and to the right of the diving backward point fielder who makes a half-stop
Violence! Simmons rushed down the track, moves outside leg and slapped the length delivery through point.

A short of length delivery on the middle stump line, Simmons shuffles across, is cramped for the room and slightly late on it as well as he tries to swat-pull. The ball moves past the waft and bounds off waist to the off side
another good delivery; on a length and bouncing towards off and middle line, Simmons edges it to his thigh pad
moves outside leg, gives himself room, and goes for a cut. No wood on leather, though.
around the leg stump line, short delivery, Simmons is again late on the swat-pull and the ball bounds off the left arm

And takes out Bravo first ball! Delivered from over the stumps, it landed outside leg stump, slightly back of length and turned right across Bravo. He went back and tried to punch it through off side. mistake. The ball turned, hit the edge and flew to first slip, where Misbah pouched a sharp catch
flighted slowly around off, defended to the on side of the pitch
gets back to dab this to the on side
presses right back to defend to the off side
turns in to the middle, nudged to midwicket region
Lovely doosra! Samuels has no clue. He went back, stabbed thin air and was lucky not to get the edge!

Loud appeal for a catch by the keeper down the leg side. It was a shortish delivery around the leg stump line, Samuels doesn't connect with this pull- just like couple of times in the last over- and the ball brushed the thigh as it went to Salman
on the pads, glanced down to fine-leg
shuffles right across the stumps to defend to point
shuffles right across and tucks it from the middle and off line to backward square-leg
short of length, outside off stump, mistimes the cut to the off side
shortish delivery on the middle and leg line, swatted to square-leg
floated well outside off and Simmons tries to sweep it from there but can't connect. It was too wide for him to attempt that.
gets back to defend this to the point region
Connects with this sweep this time and nearly got a four. hammad Azam rushes across to his right to deep  backward square-leg and makes a scrambling stop ...
taps this to square-leg region for a single

Loud appeal for lbw. A lot similar to the one that Tendulkar survived in the semi-final game.  It landed around middle and skidded towards middle and leg. Samuels was struck on the pad, missing his sweep. I thought it would have hit the leg stump. ump prob thought it would have missed the leg
dabs this behind square-leg for a single

drags this slightly short and Simmons makes it appear shorter than it was by pressing back, moving outside leg, and cuts it through extra cover. Hamam makes another fab diving save at the cover boundary
gets well back to defend the leg break to the off side
slightly short in length outside off stump, cut away to backward point
presses back to push it to the covers
The bouncing googly this time .. it turns back into the leg line, cramps the batsman, who jabs it to the off side
a leg  break this time, pushed away to cover point
slows up the pace ,tosses it up full, driven to deep cover
leans forward to push it back to the bowler
leans forward to defend it to the off side
gets back to dab this to short fine-leg region
floated outside off stump line, defended to the off side
floated full delivery, around off and middle, eased to long-on
around the off stump line, nudged to the gully region
gets well back to punch it to covers
floated well outside off stump, driven to covers
gets back to cut it away to point region
slightly short in length, pulled away for a single
Massive. It flew out of the ground! Slog swept! He thrusts his front foot forward and absolutely walloped it. The ball soared up and over. Wonder who got that souvenir.
that doosra again! Gem! Samuels has no clue again and jabs inside the line and Salman collects
gets back to dab this off break to square-leg
Now he troubles him with the off break as well. Loopy delivery turning in from outside off, Samuels is struck on the pad, as he lunges out to defend
gets back to defend to the leg side
lands on the middle stump line, straightens, pushed back down the track
works this off break on the middle and leg to backward square-leg fielder

Aha! he first shaped for the conventional sweep and as he realised that Afrid had pushed it well outside off, he changed his mind, adjusted, opened the bat-face and steered it late to third man boundary
this time plays the cut but can't beat backward point
fliighted on the middle stump line, driven back to the bowler
gets back and across to dab to point region
stays back again to dab it to the off side
stays back to defend to the off. Good news for Samuels is that he won't face Ajmal next over.
Thunderous! Simmons charges down the track and smashes it on the up and blats it over sight screen
moves round the stumps now and starts off with a full delivery, not yorker length but pretty full, Simmons is caught by surprise and just about jabs it off the inside edge on to his boot
from over the stumps, a length delivery on the middle, defended off the back foot
Wide lone slip in place and he watches Samuels tap this length delivery back to the bowler
around off stump line, Samuels defends this to the off side
slightly slower, around off, steered to point
leans forward to push to covers
fetches it from outside off to paddle it to fine-leg boundary. third ODI fifty! His highest is 70

Umar Akmal takes a stinger at short extra cover! It was floated well outside off, Simmons reached out for it and carved it really hard over that short extra cover but Umar  jumped to pouch it rather calmly! He parried the ball and caught it on the rebound.  Good knock but it's over now.
How did that miss the off stump! It was over spun and it skidded and bounced quickly outside off. Kirk stabbed nervously inside the line and missed
tries to bowl the slower on but floats it wide outside off
leans forward to defend it to the on side
pushes this to covers
Samuels stirs. He is awake, folks! He moves forward and whacks it on the up and over extra cover. he took some risk to break free.
and pushes this to long-off - Pakistan reacted to the previous boundary by pushing mid-off to long-off - for a single
angled across Kirk who is beaten, pushing well away from the body.
gets back to punch this to sweeper cover for a single that gets him off the mark
Top shot! He leaned forward and smoked through the line. He walloped a length delivery from outside off to the long-on boundary. Crashed on the up.
retains the strike with a punchy shot to deep backward point
leans forward to ease this to long-off
gets back to punch this to long-off for another run
slows up the pace, Samuels gets back to punch to right of sweeper cover
on the length outside off stump, punched away to left of backward point where Ahmad makes a diving stop
in the corridor outside off stump, straightens outside off, the batsman is beaten, pushing inside the line
gets forward to on drive to long-on
floated full outside off stump, guided to backward point
gets back to clip this from the middle stump line to deep square-leg
leans forward to drive to long-off

What a mess! It landed outside off and turned in gently. Kirk thought it would explode in and pushed nervously, well inside the line as if he anticipated it would turn in  big. Meanwhile, the ball wobbled away gently towards the off stump. Kirk tried to adjust and moved his wrists to the right. Too late. The ball fell on the off stump. Clatter!
flighted full on a length around off, turned to short midwicket
gets back to punch it to long-on
tossed up around off, pushed back off the front foot
comes forward and flicks a fuller one to midwicket
gets this one away, dropped short and he latches on, pulling it high and into the deep midwicket boundary
pushes forward for a single to long off this time
gets width outside off, lots of it, goes back and hammers it wide of sweeper cover who does well to stop the boundary with a dive
bowls it slowly through the air, on the stumps, and he gets forward to smother it
shortish and turning in from outside off, goes deep to punch to long on for a single
fuller and angled in on leg, he can't nudge it past midwicket
goes back to smash this one turning in, but cannot beat short extra cover
fuller on the stumps, played to midwicket
flicks with the turn past midwicket this time
tossed up a touch slower outside off, he shuffles across to turn it to midwicket who makes a diving stop
hustling run up to the crease, on a length and pushed to mid off
angles this one in to middle and leg, mid on in business this time
uses the angle off a fuller one to whip through midwicket
around a good length this time, outside off, and he opens the face to run it to third man
eases this one down to long on for another single
77 mph, on a length around off stump, and he pushes it out to mid off
gets back to work this to midwicket
flighted around off stump line, eased to long-on
taps this to right of the bowler who makes a good lunging stop and the keeper likes that effort
gets forward to cream this through extra cover for couple of runs
presses back to punch this to long-on
turns into the middle stump, pushed down towards long-on again
on a length around off and middle, punched down to long-on
tries to clip this through the on side, misses and is struck on the thigh pad
shout for lbw but it was going down leg. It cut in a touch from middle and leg line and Samuels loses balance as he tries to turn it to the leg side
straighter, on the middle and this time Samuels drives straight down the track
Bravo,  being wristy, plays a similar ball to midwicket

shout for lbw, turned down. This too cut in a little, like say what Abdul Razzaq would have done, and Bravo missed to connect with his drive. Thought it would have hit the leg stump. Was there an edge? Will confirm post a replay
from round the stumps, pushed to extra cover
turns this to midwicket
And again.
around the off stump line, tapped to point
on the middle and leg line, worked straight to midwicket
around the off stump line, eased to long-off for a single
around the off stump line, pushed back to the bowler
this one is on the leg stump line and it deflects off the pad to fine-leg boundary but it has been given as wides.
shorter in length, on middle and leg, worked away to deep midwicket
gentle seam-up delivery, on the middle, clipped past square-leg
leans forward and checks his drive to the off side
drifts to the pads and rolls away to the leg side. Another op missed out by Samuels
the slower delivery and Samuels is beaten on the cut by the lack of pace. It bounced once before it reached Salman, who went back for this ball. He was standing up to the stumps so far
drifts down the leg side from round the stumps.
slower, around off and middle, Bravo pings long-on
gets back to tickle this through midwicket
on the middle and leg line, punched away to long-on
on the middle stump line, slower, worked away to midwicket
gets forward to pick a single to long-off
lovely floater from round the stumps, full and drifting away nicely, Bravo is sucked forward and is beaten by the drift. He edges the drive through vacant slip region

Hammad Azam's first international wicket! Samuels has been bowled off the pads. It landed short of length and tilted in off the seam towards leg stump. Samuels had shuffled across, a touch too far, and tried to glance it but missed. The ball clipped the thigh pad and fell on the stumps.
gets back to steer this to left of backward point
around 78 mph, length delivery around off, pushed to covers for a single
gentle stuff on the middle stump line, turned past midwicket for a single
a slower one, off cutter, around off, pushed to left of straightish midwicket where Shehzad makes a fine diving stop
drifts to the pad and again, another West Indian batsman fails to connect with the flick. It rolls off the pad
in the zone outside off, extra bounce, Baugh is beaten, trying to steer it to gully
this time, he gets the horizontal shot going and chops the shortish delivery to third man

Bravo combusts! Quite an ugly shot this. He went down the track, Wahab dragged it shorter and pushed it wider, outside off. Bravo reached out, looked like he was initially going for the pull and ended up carving it up towards deep cover. Ugliness.
just outside off, stabbed away off the back foot
banged in short and Baugh hops to defend to the on side
short in length, outside off, cut away through point
on the middle and off line, defended to the off side
Slog-sweep! He cleared the front foot and smashed this over midwicket on a bent knee
short and wide, cut to left of Ajmal at sweeper cover
googly from outside off, Sammy stabs at it tentatively and it runs off the inner edge to backward square-leg
his first option was a sweep. He realised that was not on. So he decided to cut. Too late. The keeper collects
laps this around the corner to fine-leg region
tries to work it to the on side, misses but collects a leg bye
gets on the back foot to flick it behind square
turns in from outside off, Sammy was shuffling across, missed the leg glance and it rolls off the pad to fine-leg
turns in quickly from outside off, the batsman goes for the cut but is late on it and it goes off the pad and bat to off
the doosra this time but short in length, and that length allows Sammy to swat it to the on sisde
slower, tossed up off break outside off break, runs it through wide backward point
lunges forward to nudge it to backward square-leg
tossed up well outside off, driven to deep cover
skids to the middle, whipped to deep square-leg

loud cry for lbw Afriidi and Salman can't believe that its been turned down. It was the googly that broke back in from outside off stump and Baugh was clueless. He tried to cut but was cramped for room and was struck on his back thigh - the leg was bent- well inside the crease. That looks out. It would have hit the leg and middle.
pushes this out to backward point
gets back to force this to covers
turns in from outside off, pushed out to covers
a doosra from round the stumps this time and it rolls off the pad for more leg byes
turned through backward square-leg for a single
aha! That doosra again. Baugh missed it by miles! Oh dear. His bat was on the middle stump line and the ball broke away outside off!
moves outside leg, then walks back in and works it behind square-leg

Given out lbw but there was an inside edge! It was the slider on the off and middle line and Baugh pressed well back and jabbed out at it. The ball clipped the inside edge and fell on the pad. . Ump Malcolm took some time, actually looked to his right side and then put his finger up
tries the slider again, full again, edged away on the front foot
stays back to turn it to short fine-leg region
works this through to deep backward square-leg region
leg break this time, from just outside off, left alone
lunges across to defend and edges it to his pad
beaten by the doosra. again. They have no clue.
quicker outside off stump, Sammy misses the cut and Salman too fumbles
tries the doosra but drops it short and pushes it well outside off stump, and that length and width allows Sammy to punish through covers
the off break this time and it turns past the waft to hit the pad
tossed up, slower, on the off stump line, leans forward to defend
Ah! He has hit another boundary. Another doosra, again a touch short and outside off, Sammy reacted quickly, went back and punched it aerially over extra cover.
leans forward to defend to the off side
lunges across to push it to the off side
skids on towards middle, tapped to the on side
just outside the off stump, edges away to short third man
on the pads, turned down to short fine-leg
lunges forward and across to defend to the off side
yorker around off stump line,  from round the stumps, squeezed out to point
fullish, on the middle, driven to covers
slower one, steered to Akmal at backward point
fab yorker on the middle stump line, from round the stumps, dug out by Sammy, who brought that bat down in a hurry
slower one, full and outside off, Sammy slices it just over the leaping Umar Akmal at backward point
full in length around off stump, Roach plays a pretty compact-looking defensive shot
slower one, on a length around middle, pushed out to midwicket
tries another slower, slightly short in length, Sammy waits and pulls it to backward square-leg boundary
Holes out to long-on. It was a slower one, full, and Sammy lofts it straight to long-on. Sammy is upset, bangs his bat down on the ground and so is Mike Holding with that slog
full in length around off, pushed out to covers. No ball!
He has defended that free hit!  he gets behind the line and gently pats down the shortish ball. And Tony Cozier drawls, "Of course if it wasn't a free hit, they would have tried to smash it!"
gets behind the line to defend
leans forward to push this to covers
floated well outside off, Bishoo lunges and pushes at it .. well inside the line
lands outside off and turns away, left alone
flighted well outside off, full, Bishoo goes for the drive and edges it between Salman and the lunging Afridi, who was standing wide

Killing me softly is the song in the air! What a tame dismissal. he tried to turn it to the leg side and the ball gently wobbled back off the leading edge. Ajmal took the dolly, and kept the ball on the ground and quietly walked away.
Just outside off stump and Martin pushes inside the line. Salman collects.
If the top order couldn't pick the doosra how is the tail going to do it. Martin is beaten again
gets back to defend this to the leg side
taps this to right of midwicket
slings a very full delivery past the attempted dab and past the off stump
fullish around off stump line, scooped over - he was trying to whip it to the on side- the leaping bowler for a single
Shout for lbw, turned down. It pitched on the leg stump line and straightened to hit him on the leg stump line. It would have clipped the leg stump and hawk eye agrees.
in the zone outside off, cut and a miss
gets back to punch to covers
That same-old story. doosra. Stab in the air. The keeper collects.
around the leg stump line, nurdled to backward square-leg fielder
from round the stumps, another doosra that goes away from the off stump, he tries to sweep but misses
this doosra turns in from outside leg, moves past the sweep and hits the pad
Oh well. You know what happened here. Yep, the doosra that goes past the defensive push
fullish, turned wide of midwicket for a single
slower one, full and outside off, Roach has a waft, the bat hit the ground and the ball wobbled past the edge
the lifter this time, Roach just about manages to jab it to the leg side
full and well outside off, slashed to third man
full and just outside off, square driven to cover point
the bouncer around the leg stump line, the batsman goes down under
from round the stumps, floated outside off, defended on the front foot
turns in to the middle stump line, Roach is cramped but manages to jab it to the on side
plays the sweep to pick up a single
Yet another doosra which breaks away sharply past the defensive push
quicker one, straight on the off, edged away to point
tossed up outside off, full and again, the batsman is beaten
moves outside leg, Wahab tries to follow him and Roach drags it through wide midwicket. Hamad Azam tried to make a sliding save but his foot touched the boundary ropes
slower one, loopy, dipping full on the leg stump line, Roach waited and waited before he glided it neatly to fine-leg boundary
in the zone outside off, pushed through point
full length delivery around off, pushed out to covers
on the middle, whipped away to deep midwicket
yorker on the middle, squeezed out wide of midwicket
slower one aorund off stump line, pushed to right of Umar Akmal at point. Akmal fires a throw at non-striker's end and misses. And then they take the overthrows
pushes this down to long-on
overpitched on the legs, whipped to deep midwicket
Whoa! he has smashed that. Roach clears the front foot and tonks this length delivery over wide long-on
moves outside leg and has a big heave at this very full delivery but doesn't connect. The ball goes between him and the leg stump
Roach is run out. It was mistime to the left of Azam who stops it and then breaks the stumps.

inn2.comm: cuts in towards the pads, around 85 mph, moves past the waft and rolls off the pad
around the off stump line, nudged out to the off
in the channel outside off, left alone
from wide of the crease, a length delivery just outside off, squired to third man
holds its line outside off and bounces extra, flies off the edge through gully to third man
leans forward to deflect this to midwicket
just short of length, around off stump, pushed out to point
on the middle and leg line, short in length, clipped through backward square-leg region
short in length outside off stump, cut away through point. Nicely done.
in the channel outside off sutmp, left alone
gets forward to deflect it to midwicket
short in length outside off stump, pushed back to the bowler
around the off stump line, defended on the back foot
short in length, around the off and middle, turned to midwicket
around the off stump line, defended towards covers
shortish delivery outside off, run down to third man
full in length and in the zone outside off stump, he is beaten on the drive.. the ball rushes past the edge
short in length, moves in to the off, defended out to the off side
short in length and outside off stump, carved away to third man
on the middle and leg line, nurdled through backward square-leg
slip and leg slip in place, and he pushes out the full delivery to cover
in the channel outside off stump, left alone
back of length outside off, holds its line and so Shehzad reaches out to push it back down the track
works this towards mid-off and gets across for a quick single
straightens around off stump, from back of length, stabbed through covers
on a length, on the middle, turned to the leg side
from wide of the crease, short in length on the off, pushed back down the track
stays back to push a length delivery to covers
fuller, around off, straightens a touch, driven out to mid-off
Ah! lovely punchy shot! It kicked up from short of length, he rode the bounce and punched it sweetly through cover point. Super
full and well outside off stump, left alone
pushes it wider outside off, left alone
cut in to the middle stump line, defended to the on side of the pitch
full in length outside off stump, pushed through cover point
short in length outside off, carved away to point
leans forward to punch the length delivery back to the bowler
in the zone outside off, left alone
gets solidly behind the line to defend to the off side
banged in short, around off, swatted to mid-on
full in length, on the middle and off line, defended to the on side
in the channel outside off stump, left alone
shortish delivery outside off, he tries to have a go at it but doesn't connect
short in length and outside off, edged to the pad
leans forward to push it back down the track
fullish outside off stump line, left alone
gets forward to work this wide of mid-on for a single
slightly slower, outside off, pushed out to covers
leans forward to deflect it of wide mid-on
gets forward to deflect to the midwicket
short in length outside off stump, pushed out to mid-on
short in length, on outside off stump, swatted to midwicket
back of length around off stump line, pushed out to mid-off
short in length outside off, shoved away through midwicket
full in length outside off stump, driven to sweeper cover
length delivery around off stump, pushed out to short extra cover
slightly slower one, around the off and middle line, turned towards midwicket for a quick single
fullish, on the middle and leg line, flicked uppishly to the right of the diving short midwicket fielder
Dropped by Dwayne Bravo.  A full delivery outside off stump, driven uppishly and hard over short extra cover where Dwayne jumps up but it bursts through his palms.
gets forward to defend this
leans well forward to drive to mid-off
pushes it wide outside off and Ump Malcolm signals
length delivery around off stump line, turned away wide of mid-on
full in length on the middle stump line, pushed down to mid-on
around the off stump line, steered to cover point
cuts in to the middle stump line, pushed back to the bowler
length delivery outside off stump, cut away to backward point
full in length outside off stump, pushed down to mid-off
slower one, full and outside off, pushed to left of mid-off
banged in short around off, swatted to midwicket
full in length, around middle, pushed out to mid-on
short in length outside off stump, run down to third man
leans well forward to defend it to short extra cover
fullish around the pads, flicked away through midwicket
short in length outside off, punched away to deep cover

But the ball turned away and bounced a touch extra and he couldn't control his shot. he ended up carving it to backward point. Another template innings from Hafeez: get a start, throw it away.

Shafiq is run out Or is he? It was pushed to point region and Shehzad sets off for the run before he changed his mind. Shafiq had rushed too far across. The fielder came in from backward point and threw to the bowler. Martin lunges to his left to collect it but here begins the drama. He reaches to break the stumps but he missed it! he then lunged again to find the stumps and the bail just about lifted before the bat came inside the crease. It appeared very close. Out is the verdict
